paragraphs.body: Born and raised in Hollywood, California, Darcy Rose Byrnes is the daughter of actors Cathy D'Arcy and CJ Byrnes.
paragraphs.text: Born and raised in Hollywood, California, Darcy Rose Byrnes is the daughter of actors Cathy D'Arcy and CJ Byrnes.

paragraphs.body: Byrnes appeared in the direct-to-video film The Sparky Chronicles: The Map in 2003. That same year, she landed a role in the soap opera The Young and the Restless as Abby Carlton, a role she would continue to play until 2008. During that time, she also had a guest starring role in The Bold and the Beautiful for eight episodes. Byrnes also has appeared in television shows, including How I Met Your Mother, Ghost Whisperer, Cold Case, Dirty Sexy Money, House, and Desperate Housewives. She played Rebecca Knepp in the Hallmark Television movie, Amish Grace, alongside Kimberly Williams-Paisley, and also provides the speaking and singing voice of Princess Amber in Sofia the First.
